name: Ariana
title: Manager
blurbs: Hi!! I am Ariana Johnson a fourth year Muir College student studying Human Biology and Public Health. I am an awkward individual, but absolutely loe having conversations and am more than happy to answer any coffee related questions, give any suggestions on fun coffee shops to explore, or even ponder the meaning of life with you. But I must warn you I am sarcastic about 95% of the time and love to joke around so please don't take me too seriously.

name: Aleesha
blurbs: What's up everybody! My name is Aleesha, and I'm a fourth year ICAM major with a double minor in Psychology and Studio Art. I love to sing, whether I'm messing around on my ukulele or jamming with my acapella group, the Tritones. This is my third year working at the Muir College Center. I love this place and the community of Muir. If you're an early morning cup of coffee type person, I'll be seeing you around! Come say hello during my opening shift!

name: Natalie
blurbs: I'm Natalie Rhoades, a third year Marine Biology major from Muir College. This is my second year working at Muir Woods so I'm on the lookout for my regulars, especially during Monday night's Happy Hour, 7-9pm! My favorite drink on the menu is a classic latte complete with a little foam art - I've been practicing. Don't forget to come visit me during my shifts! I'll be playing my favorite old-school hip hop, Carlos Santana, and Jack Johnson. Here's to a fantastically caffeinated year!

name: Brianna
blurbs: Hi, I'm Brianna! I'm a second year Muir College student majoring in Communication with a double minor in Sociology and Creative Writing. I'm also a freelance photographer, an avid astrology geek, and a fan of rock music. I moved to California from a small town in Florida, so something you may notice about me is my Southern hospitality - I want to make you feel at home!

name: Liza
blurbs: Hi everyone! I'm Liza and I am a third year Warren student who has been adopted by Muir Woods. I am a Human Biology major and a Cognitive Science minor, and I'm alwys excited to talk about the brain and human body. It's my goal this year to figure out how to make a rainbow layered blended latte - I'm really into baking and I'm borrowing inspiration from a rainbow cake I've made before. Catch me at Muir in the mornings - my favorite time of the day, and I'll help you start your day off caffeinated and upbeat!

name: Maryam
blurbs: Hello! My name is Maryam. I am a second year Political Science International Relations major with a business minor. I love to travel, especially when elephants will be involved. My goal in life is to be an awesome lawyer and save the world a little bit. I am in a committed relationship with nice sunsets and the beach. I am also a proud Foosher and lover of comedy so feel free to drop by with your cheesiest joke or best pun!

name: Neha
blurbs: Hello! My name is Neha Sodhi, and I am a second year BIoengineering: Biotechnology major from Muir College. This is my first year behind the counter at Muir Woods, and I could not be more excited to be here and seving up the fantastic espresso and coffee that turned me into a caffeine addict. I absolutely adore puns, so feel free to drop by and give me your best pun or geeky pick up line. Bonus points if it's Harry Potter, science or food inspired!

name: Paul
blurbs: Hello, my name is Paul. I am a 3rd year Psychology major with minors in both Business and Photography. Weird fun facts about me are that I subconsciously shake my hips.dance in my seat when I am eating because it is when I am happiest and I have been known to touch my nose instead of my chin when I am thinking or studying. I can never study in my own apartment, so I like studying at coffee shops with a vanilla latte in hand and I am always in the mood for a good pun. Stop by and say hi!
